Definition 2.4. Let $I$ and $\mathcal{A}$ be $2$-categories, and let $F\colon I\to\mathcal{A}$ be a $2$-functor. A $2$-limit of $F$ comprises the data of a object $L\in\mathcal{A}$ together with a $2$-natural transformation $\lambda\colon\Delta L\Rightarrow F$, which are such that, for each object $X\in\mathcal{A}$, the functor ${\lambda_{*}\circ\Delta}\colon{\mathcal{A}(X,L)}\rightarrow{[I,\mathcal{A}](% \Delta X,F)}$ given by post-composition with $\lambda$ is an isomorphism of categories.
